  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">According to statistics, China has 20% of the world&apos;s blind population. The least fortunate among the blind are the blind orphans. Launched in 2003, Bethel is a not-for-profit organization which focuses on empowering the visually impaired Chinese orphan community by providing foster care, education, therapy, and livelihood opportunities. Bethel&apos;s school provides our blind and visually impaired orphans the education necessary so that one day they can lead a fulfilling, independent life.</narrative>
  </description>
